# Repo Hygiene

## Track in git

- Source, tests, docs, CI workflows, `*.example` configs, lockfiles
- Generated design-token outputs only when committed intentionally (prefer CI regen)

## Never track

- `node_modules/`, `.venv/`, `dist/`, `build/`, `target/`, `coverage/`, `.gradle/`, caches
- `.env` (keep `.env.example`)
- Live copies: `.app-update.json`, `donations.json` (use `.example` in repo)
- OS junk: `.DS_Store`, `Thumbs.db`

## Agent commit discipline

1. Review `git status` before every commit
2. Stage **explicit paths** — avoid blind `git add -A`
3. Run `bash scripts/check-repo-hygiene.sh` before push (CI runs the same gate)
4. Reclaim disk: `bash scripts/purge-ephemeral.sh` (dry-run); `--apply` uses `git clean -fdX` (ignored only)

## Policies

- **No Git LFS** or **submodules** without `[HUMAN]` approval
- Build outputs publish via CI artifacts (GitHub Pages, Releases) — not git history
- See `docs/REPO_HYGIENE.md` for full automation map
